	<Body>
		<Section>
			<SectionHead />
			<HTML>
				&lt;p&gt;
Oil of oregano has received a lot of attention, with proponents claiming it can treat a variety of illnesses, including sinus disorders. Like many spices, oregano does have some antibacterial and antifungal properties &amp;mdash; making it at least plausible that it might help or prevent some sinus problems caused by bacteria and fungi.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Unfortunately, there have been no published trials that have looked at oil of oregano specifically for this use. For this reason, it isn&apos;t known what role, if any, oil of oregano plays in treating or preventing sinusitis. 
&lt;/p&gt;
			</HTML>
		</Section>
	</Body>
	<Title>
		Oil of oregano: Can it treat sinusitis?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Oregano is thought to have antibacterial and antifungal properties.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		I&apos;ve heard that oil of oregano is effective in relieving and preventing sinusitis. Is this true?
	</Question>
